While conceptually simple, empirically, these enable effective routing with a dynamic LLM pool across several benchmarks. In sum, our contributions are:

1. we formalise the problem setting of model routing with a dynamic pool of LLMs (§3);
2. we propose UniRoute (§4.1), a novel routing approach relying on an LLM feature representation based on its prediction error vector on a small set of representative prompts (§4.2);
3. we propose two simple yet effective instantiations of UniRoute based on unsupervised or supervised clustering (§5.1, §5.2, Figure 1), with an accompanying excess risk bound (§5.3);
4. we present experiments (§7) on EmbedLLM [Zhuang et al., 2024], SPROUT o3-mini [Somerstep et al., 2025], RouterBench [Hu et al., 2024b], and Chatbot Arena [Ong et al., 2025], illustrating the ability to effectively route amongst > 30 unseen LLMs.
